title: Bonnie and Clyde (1967) (Warren Beatty, Faye Dunaway)
description:
BONNIE AND CLYDE - 1967

IMDb Rating: 8.0
http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0061418/

  Bonnie and Clyde is an unforgettable classic that has lost none of its power since its 1967 release.
  Warren Beatty and Faye Dunaway are the legendary Depression-era bandits and lovers in this landmark film that won two Academy Awards and helped trigger a revolution in screen violence. The film is a poetic ode to the Great Depression, as the titular antiheroes (Bonnie & Clyde), barrel across the South and Midwest robbing banks with Clyde's brother Buck (Gene Hackman), Buck's frantic wife Blanche (Estelle Parsons), and their faithful accomplice C.W. Moss (the inimitable Michael J. Pollard).

  Starring: Warren Beatty, Faye Dunaway, Michael J. Pollard, Gene Hackman, Estelle Parsons. (and Gene Wilder in his first movie)

  Directed by: Arthur Penn.

  Quality: Very Good Xvid from DVD.

  Length: 1hr. 47min.

  Language: English.

  Size: 688 x 400
